reviewText:
You can't help but LOVE Osa Johnson!  An incredible soul with an incredible life that cannot be replaced in history.  Her and Mr Johnson have never been given enough credit for their work.  I cannot wait to make it their museum to appreciate in more depth.
Movie is a great tribute!
nice to go back in time

The narrator is so 50's Disney-esque as to be annoying and unbelievable.  I wanted to see the films taken by Martin & Osa Johnson, but the re-enactments distract from the original footage.  I'd really like to see their original films organized as a document of natural history rather than as a biography.
